Plectranthus esculentus

   [8753.jpg]
   Authority N.E. Br.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Asteridae:Lamiales:Labiatae
   Synonyms Coleus dazo, Coleus esculentus, Coleus floribundus, Coleus
   floribundus var longipes, Englerastrum floribundum, Englerastrum
   floribundum var longipes, Plectranthus floribundus
   Common names coleus potato, Livingstone potato, wilde aartappel,
   shezha, tsenga, tensa, tsenza, mutada, matheta, makwele, tapole emahlo,
   tapole-ea-mahlo, itapile, ibonda, ugilo, potato - coleus, ulucanqu,
   uluhlaza, isiqwili, ushizane, umhlati, ulujilo, umbondive, imbondwe,
   ujwangu, ushizan, UJilo, UJikwe, UHlazaluti, IZambhane
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 8753

   Notes
   SOURCES (P. esculentus N.E.Br.)
   Tindall H 1983 pp 241-243 [USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 24 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 466 [USE]
   Purseglove 1974 pp 636 [USE]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial herb, tubers may be harvested 180-200 days from planting.
   COMMON NAMES
   Livingstone potato, Hausa potato, Kaffir potato, Umbondive, Rizga,
   Buye, Nyumbu, Njowe, Cezani.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonyms: P. floribundus, Coleus dazo, C. esculentus. Native
   to tropical Africa, possibly south-east Africa. Recorded yields are in
   the region of 2-6 t/ha.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
